### UX_ANTIPATTERNS
- Wall-of-errors: aggregate by rule with counts, then one top fix; existing validation already summarizes errors/warnings separately `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh:920`.
- Cryptic failures: every new validator entry needs `How to Fix` wording like existing rules, not just a rule id `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:415`.
- Blocking fresh scaffold: AC coverage must honor lifecycle opt-in because new L2 specs can have zero tests at scaffold time `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/006-peck-source-deep-mining/research.md:101`.
- Double-prompting: use skill-advisor/startup briefs for passive context only; hooks surface compact routing and fail open, not blocking prompts `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md:24`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md:83`.
- Verdict ambiguity: keep exact PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL strings parseable; deep-review automation depends on exact final-line parsing `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml:1221`.

